  "identifier": "trusted-loop",
  "name": "Trusted-Loop Mode",
  "description": "A Claude Code plugin that keeps an unattended AI coding agent working until an independent ensemble of LLM judges confirms the task is complete, verified against fresh behavioral evidence (test/build/lint output) and a fixed definition of done — not the agent's own claim. Judges run independently and in parallel for decorrelation; aggregation is by evidence, not votes.",
